  "text": "[22] The horizontal extent of the forest area that contributes 80% of all fluxes was estimated by applying the algorithm proposed by [CITATION_1] to each data record. In this algorithm the 80% cumulative contribution distance increases with measurement height and with increasing stability, and decreases with surface roughness and increasingly unstable conditions. These distances were plotted against the associated wind direction on a polar plot and the symbols coded according to the associated sensible heat fluxes. This creates a two-dimensional picture of the shape of the area ''seen'' by the towers over time.",
